Source: WHO SARS website/Beijing Government SARS website [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/sars/chinatable2003_06_3.pdf>
<http://www.beijing.gov.cn/english/englishsars/beijingen/detail.asp?ResourceID=63257>

[The Beijing Government SARS website link is changed daily, but the
WHO website maintains each daily report in archives. - Mod.MPP]
The cumulative total of probable cases reported to date is 5329, with
3 new cases reported in the past 24 hours. There are an additional
929 suspected cases pending (down from 982 on 1 Jun 2003 and 965 on 2
Jun 2003, representing exclusions of reported suspected cases).
There have been 3 new suspected cases reported in the previous 24
hours, of which 2 were reported from Beijing and 1 from Guangdong. In
the past 24 hours there have been no new deaths attributable to SARS
reported, leaving the total number of deaths attributable to SARS at
334.
A map of current probable cases can be found at:
<http://www.who.int/csr/sars/map_china_2003_06_03.gif>
