[As of 3 Jun 2003, there have been a cumulative total of 8398
probable cases of SARS with 772 deaths reported to WHO from 29
countries. In the past 24 hours since the last WHO update, there
have been 22 new probable cases of SARS reported, of which 15 were
from Canada, 3 from China, 2 from the United States, and 1 each from
Hong Kong and Taiwan. According to the Health Canada update, in the
24-hour period since the last update, there have been 4 new probable
and 4 new suspected cases reported with most recent dates of onset 31
May 2003 and 28 May 2003, respectively.
The WHO update today mentions that caution should be exercised in
interpreting the decrease in reported cases from China. There are
concerns about the "the sensitivity of case detection in some
provinces, and about the capacity of the health infrastructure to
cope with a challenge on the scale of SARS." There is a strong
statement in the update that China is considered to be the epicenter
of this outbreak, and that unless transmission in China is
interrupted, there may be continued seeding of outbreaks outside of
China due to high population flow/movement. - Mod.MPP]
